    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-05-01T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-05-01T09:00:00-05:00" n="601"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d601">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">684A.85/5–153: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 601<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Israel (<persName corresp="#p_RFH1" type="from"
                            >Russell</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d601fn1">Repeated to Amman, Jerusalem, London, Paris, Cairo,
                        Beirut, Damascus, Baghdad, and Jidda.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tel Aviv</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-05-01T17:00:00+03:00"
                            >May 1, 1953—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1688. I informed Director General Foreign Ministry <persName corresp="#p_EW1"
                        >Eytan</persName> yesterday of our views on proposal for high level talks on
                    border problems (point 4, Department telegram 962).<note n="2" xml:id="d601fn2">
                        <ref target="#d600">
                            <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> He voiced Israel Government’s warm support.</p>
                <p>Re point 3, reference telegram <persName corresp="#p_EW1">Eytan</persName>
                    categorically denied that <gloss target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss> had been refused
                    access to six wounded Israelis saying in fact no such request had been made.
                    Gave assurances that if request made Israel will accede immediately.</p>
                <p>While setting up three separate Jordan-Israel <gloss target="#t_MAC1"
                    >MAC</gloss>s (point 5 reference telegram) would not solve problem of
                    infiltration it would: <list>
                        <label>(1)</label>
                        <item>Reduce delays due to clogging of <gloss target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss>
                            machinery;</item>
                        <label>(2)</label>
                        <item>Bring more observers into the field presumably closer to scene of
                            incidents;</item>
                        <label>(3)</label>
                        <item>Demonstrate the <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> far from taking
                            seriously attempts to discredit <gloss target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss>s is
                            determined support and strengthen them.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Decision would, of course, presuppose ability and willingness both parties spare
                    competent personnel for <gloss target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss> duty, and would be
                    constructive contribution only if additional <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>
                    observers were carefully selected with eye to special problems in area. Plan
                    might involve in addition to increase in number of <gloss target="#t_UN1"
                        >UN</gloss> observers, individual chairman for each new <gloss
                        target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RFH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
